The paper discusses a simulation model for exploring the relation between the number of submissions and the overall standard of academic journals within a similar discipline under peer review. This involves distributed parallel systems, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and possibly digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis of academic journals falls under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
